reviewText: These CD's were great for the grandkids and offered a wholesome viewing experience for them without the worry of a bad word sneaking in.

When my art teacher brought this DVD in, I loved it. My favorite episodes are Troy Black Junior High and The Great Cookie Calamity. I like it when the boss says "Jacobs, roll the film". My favorite actor is Shannon Ozimey. I once tried to write a story but I forgot they're out of buisness. I have numbers 1,3, and 4 (this one), but for some reason they didn't have 2. I got this at 99 Cents Stuff. If I happen to find the others. I will certanly review them. Amazon, roll the review!
